--- title: "Perfective forms of the verb ‘do’" author: "Nina Dobrushina" date: 2025-08-28 format: html css: styles.css --- The perfective form of the verb 'do' varies across dialects. In Gender 1 the most frequent variant is hɨʔɨ-, the other attested variants include jɨʔɨ-, and haq'ɨ-. In Gender 2 The most frequent variant is rɨʔɨ-, the other attested variants include harɨ-, harq'ɨ- and harʔɨ-.
